 wrong – yet not need any foundation outside themselves","duration":0,"creditsShort":null,"commentsEnabled":false,"settings":{"badgeColor":"white","cardPlayIconColor":"white","alignX":"right","alignY":"center","backdropStrength":3},"tags":[],"authors":[{"id":"180412","displayName":"Andrew Sepielli"}],"image":{"url":"https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/32f33fe3-c3d4-422b-a4ff-9ff7f901c177/essay-lon93507.jpg","alt":"","height":1252,"width":2000},"primaryTopic":{"title":"Ethics","slug":"ethics"},"topics":[{"slug":"ethics","title":"Ethics"},{"slug":"values-beliefs","title":"Values and beliefs"},{"slug":"metaphysics","title":"Metaphysics"}],"section":{"title":"Philosophy","slug":"philosophy"},"createdAt":"2023-10-03T11:22:08Z"},{"id":"6050","title":"Both one and yet distinct","slug":"being-a-twin-helpfully-cracks-open-our-ideas-of-individuality","type":"essay","audio":null,"standfirstShort":"Being a twin helpfully cracks open our ideas of individuality","standfirstLong":"Being a twin (as our author knows) cracks open our ideas of the perfectly bounded self and might liberate us all","duration":0,"creditsShort":null,"commentsEnabled":false,"settings":{"badgeColor":"white","cardPlayIconColor":"white","alignX":"right","alignY":"top","backdropStrength":3},"tags":[],"authors":[{"id":"59986","displayName":"Helena de Bres"}],"image":{"url":"https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/bb604a12-b526-4825-b4db-c97ed06be99c/essay-par401449.jpg","alt":"Two dark haired twin girls in tartan dresses look through an unglazed window frame","height":1252,"width":2000},"primaryTopic":{"title":"Metaphysics","slug":"metaphysics"},"topics":[{"slug":"metaphysics","title":"Metaphysics"},{"slug":"family-life","title":"Family life"},{"slug":"love-friendship","title":"Love and friendship"}],"section":{"title":"Philosophy","slug":"philosophy"},"createdAt":"2023-10-13T11:10:17Z"},{"id":"6051","title":"What is it like to be a crab?","slug":"are-we-ready-to-study-consciousness-in-crabs-and-the-like","type":"ess